      "role": "user",
      "content": "the greedy approach seems a bit risky if it causes backtracking. what are some better ways to handle it if we want to be more accurate? maybe something more advanced than just picking the nearest neighbor? like, how do we actually improve the route after the initial greedy pass?",
      "source": "evaluator"
